Officials in Ivory Coast say at least four people have been killed by a group
of armed men attacking a military police post in the country's main city.
The attack occurred Saturday in Anyama, a suburb of Abidjan. Reuters news
agency quotes an unidentified military policemen saying the four men were all
gendarmes.
The small west African nation has been plagued by violence since a 2002 civil
war that virtually split the country in two.
